<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-20T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-20T09:00:00-05:00" n="574" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/141: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1" type="from">Atherton</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-20T15:00:00+01:00">August 20,
                                1932—3 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received August 20—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>245. I discussed your 220, August 15, 6 p.m., with <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> today who said there would be no
                        difficulty. He explained “Organizing Committee is really a committee of
                        states rather than a committee of nominated individuals, and consequently in
                        view of the fact that <pb facs="0942" n="822" xml:id="pg_822"/> United
                        States Government has agreed to join the Organizing Committee an
                        announcement from Washington that United States Government nominates as its
                        representative Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SFM1">Sackett</persName>
                        with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Norman Davis</persName> as alternate or
                        associate would be quite in order”.</p>
                    <p>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> spoke of third week in
                        September either Geneva or London as possible date for first meeting of
                        Organizing Committee.</p>
                    <p>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John</persName> is en route to Lossiemouth
                        and then to Balmoral before returning to London.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_AR1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                            </persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>